  },

  "design_rationale": {
    "information_density": "MetricTile height cut ~50% — 6 metrics now fit 1 row on 1440px. Sparkline replaces wasted whitespace. Module rows replace 4-field cards: 9 fields per row, 9 modules visible without scroll.",
    "visual_hierarchy": "Three tiers. Tier 1: large mono metric values with color glow (eye lands here). Tier 2: card titles + accent bars (orient user). Tier 3: label/subvalue in white/25-35 opacity (readable but recedes). SectionTitle uses 2px gradient bar instead of heavy heading.",
    "glassmorphism": "glass utility: 72% opacity surface + blur(12px) + 8% white border. glass-strong for overlapping contexts. Accent top-bar on MetricTile and left-bar on DataCard add color without noise.",
    "micro_animations": "fadeUp keyframe (6px translate + opacity) staggers per component via animationDelay prop. LoadBar uses CSS transition-all 500ms. StatusPill dots use animate-pulse. All animations respect prefers-reduced-motion if added to globals.",
    "premium_feel": "Geist Mono for all numeric values. 10px uppercase tracking-wider table headers (Vercel pattern). Hover states: bg-white/[0.02] row highlight + ChevronRight reveal. Thin 1px borders at white/5-14 opacity keep structure without weight.",
    "component_contracts": "All props preserved. MetricTile adds optional sparkline/animationDelay. DataCard adds optional compact/noPadding/accent. StatusPill gains xs size. No breaking changes to existing consumers."
  }
}
```

---

**Key decisions:**

`ModuleRow` — 9 fields horizontal vs old 4-field card. Module table header row makes it scannable like Linear's issue list.

`MetricTile` — `text-2xl` value + sparkline in header slot. Total height ~96px vs old ~160px. Six fit in one grid row.

`DataCard` — removed padding-heavy body, added `compact` prop (p-3 vs p-4), `noPadding` for table children. Accent left-bar 2px gradient replaces colored header backgrounds.

`glass` utility — `rgba(13,17,28,0.72)` not `#0d111c` solid — allows depth layering without full opacity blocks.

`--border-subtle/default/strong` at rgba white — scales correctly against any background without hardcoded hex.

Stagger delays on grid children: visual reads left-to-right top-to-bottom, not all-at-once pop.

